rs) bring late-romantic music to thousands of listeners who have never set foot in a concert hall. Reclaiming Late-Romantic Music sheds new light on these often unfairly disparaged works and explores the historical dimension of their continuing role in the contemporary sound world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 0aMusicy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  abloch.  aclassical music.  aclaude debussy.  acontemporary music.  acontinued influence.  aearly 20th century music.  aearly modern period.  aenglish composer.  aernest bloch lectures series.  afilm music idiom.  afinnish composer.  afrederick delius.  afrench composer.  agiacomo puccini.  agustav mahler.  aitalian opera.  ajohan julius christian sibelius.  alate 19th century music.  alate romantic music.  amass culture.  amodernism.  amodernity.  amusic.  aopera composer.  aopera music.  aromantic composers.  aromantic period.  asecond world war.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028039740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095803640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520958036423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520958036/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY